In [4]:
df['ad_date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['ad_date'])

df_2021 = df[df['ad_date'].dt.year == 2021]

daily_spend = df_2021.groupby(df_2021['ad_date'].dt.date)['total_spend'].sum()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
daily_spend.plot()
plt.title('2021 Yılındaki Günlük Reklam Harcamaları')
plt.xlabel('Tarih')
plt.ylabel('Toplam Harcama')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()
In [5]:
# Make sure to use .loc to modify the DataFrame directly and avoid the SettingWithCopyWarning
df_2021.loc[:, 'total_value'] = df_2021.groupby('ad_date')['total_value'].transform('sum')
df_2021.loc[:, 'total_spend'] = df_2021.groupby('ad_date')['total_spend'].transform('sum')

# Calculate ROMI for each ad_date
df_2021.loc[:, 'ROMI'] = df_2021['total_value'] / df_2021['total_spend']

# Group by ad_date and calculate the mean ROMI
daily_romi = df_2021.groupby('ad_date')['ROMI'].mean()

# Plot daily ROMI
plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
daily_romi.plot()
plt.title('2021 Yılındaki Günlük ROMI')
plt.xlabel('Tarih')
plt.ylabel('ROMI')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

# 7 günlük hareketli ortalama
daily_spend_rolling = daily_spend.rolling(window=7).mean()
daily_romi_rolling = daily_romi.rolling(window=7).mean()

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
plt.plot(daily_spend, label='Günlük Harcama')
plt.plot(daily_spend_rolling, label='7 Günlük Hareketli Ortalama Harcama', linestyle='--')
plt.title('2021 Yılındaki Günlük Harcama ve Hareketli Ortalama')
plt.xlabel('Tarih')
plt.ylabel('Harcamalar')
plt.legend()
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.show()

plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
plt.plot(daily_romi, label='Günlük ROMI')

df['total_value'] = df.groupby('campaign_name')['total_value'].transform('sum')
df['total_spend'] = df.groupby('campaign_name')['total_spend'].transform('sum')

df['ROMI'] = df['total_value'] / df['total_spend']

campaign_romi = df.groupby('campaign_name')['ROMI'].mean()
